                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><xi:include href="../encodingdesc.xml" parse="xml"/></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_ʒorǧa" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><form type="lemma"><orth>ʒorǧa</orth></form><usg><lang/></usg><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>иноходь</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>amble</q></abv:tr></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>ʒorǧa kænun</orth></form><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>бежать иноходью</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>amble (v.)</q></abv:tr></sense><note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">; ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sīryn"/> | %iserun%i</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">; cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sīryn"/> | %iserun%i</note></re><abv:exampleGrp><abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>ʒorǧa beræ, kosgæ ba neci</quote><abv:tr xml:lang="ru"><q>иноходи (беготни) много, работы же никакой</q></abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en"><q>there is a lot of ambling (running), and there is no any working</q></abv:tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_SD"/><biblScope>293%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></abv:example></abv:exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Из <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>jorǧa</w></mentioned>; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>jūrǧa</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>iorǧa</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>jorǧa</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/> <w>jirǧa</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/> <w>jorǧä</w> <gloss><q>иноходь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><w/> <gloss><q>иноходец</q></gloss></mentioned>. Осетинский отражает джекающую тюркскую форму <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>ǯorǧa</w></mentioned> (ср. в этом отношении <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ʒylar"/> ‘недоуздок’ и др.).</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>jorǧa</w></mentioned>; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>jūrǧa</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>iorǧa</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/> <w>jorǧa</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="lez"><lang/> <w>jirǧa</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><lang/> <w>jorǧä</w> <gloss><q>amble</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-vaynakh"><w/> <gloss><q>ambler</q></gloss></mentioned>. Ossetic reflects a special Turkic form <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>ǯorǧa</w></mentioned> (cf. in this respect <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ʒylar"/> ‘halter’ etc.).</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>